This paper deals with sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural networks for learning and prediction, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval (IR) and text classification, which could place it in cs.IR. Finally, the paper mentions using attention-based methods, which are commonly used in computer vision (CV), suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CV.
